  "title": "[PERM] Account Manager (Enterprise & Government Accounts)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Manage a portfolio of premium accounts as the primary contact, driving revenue growth and market share.</li><li>Develop and execute strategic account plans to increase adoption of company’s printing, visual communications, and sustainability solutions.</li><li>Build strong relationships with C-level, IT, procurement, and business stakeholders, positioning company as a trusted partner.</li><li>Apply consultative, solution-based selling to address customer needs and support digital transformation.</li><li>Collaborate with channel partners and internal teams to ensure effective solution delivery and customer experience.</li><li>Track account performance, pipeline, forecasts, and customer satisfaction; provide regular management reports.</li></ul><p><br /><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree in Business, Marketing, IT, or related field preferred.</li><li>Minimum 5 years’ experience in enterprise account management, preferably in IT, AV, or\noffice automation.</li><li>Strong knowledge of enterprise IT/AV solutions and experience selling to large\norganizations or government agencies.</li><li>Proven ability to grow accounts and meet or exceed revenue targets.</li><li>Excellent relationship management, communication, presentation, and negotiation skills.</li></ul><p></p><p>Please state your availability, current and expected salary in the resume.<br /></p><p>We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified. </p><p>GMP Technologies (S) Pte Ltd   |   EA Licence: 11C3793   |  Eddie Tang |   Registration No: R1221129</p>",
